---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const title = 'Privacy Policy - Gemini Automator'
const lastUpdated = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
    year: 'numeric',
    month: 'long',
    day: 'numeric',
})
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
    <main
        class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-20 bg-zinc-50 dark:bg-zinc-900 rounded-2xl my-8"
    >
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 gradient-text">{title}</h1>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-8">
            Last Updated: {lastUpdated}
        </p>

        <div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
            <p>
                Your privacy is critically important to us. "Gemini Automator"
                is a Chrome Extension built by Blake Young. This privacy policy
                describes how your personal information is collected, used, and
                shared when you use the Gemini Automator extension.
            </p>

            <h3>1. Data Collection and Usage</h3>
            <p>
                <strong
                    >We do not transmit your personal data to any external
                    servers.</strong
                > The Gemini Automator extension operates locally on your device.
                Any data you input (such as prompts for the queue) resides within
                your local browser storage and is sent directly to Google's Gemini
                web interface as per your actions.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Local Storage:</strong> We use Chrome's local storage
                    API to save your queue settings and preferences. This data remains
                    on your machine and is not synced to our servers.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Interactions:</strong> The extension automates interactions
                    with the Google Gemini website. It does not read or collect data
                    from other websites you visit.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>2. Third-Party Services</h3>
            <p>
                This extension interacts with Google Gemini. By using this
                extension, you are also subject to Google's Terms of Service and
                Privacy Policy as you interact with their platform.
            </p>

            <h3>3. Permissions</h3>
            <p>
                We request the minimum permissions necessary for the extension
                to function:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Storage:</strong> To save your automation queue and settings.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Scripting/ActiveTab:</strong> To interact with the Gemini
                    page and automate your prompts.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Changes to This Policy</h3>
            <p>
                We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you
                are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We
                will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy
                on this page.
            </p>

            <h3>5. Contact Us</h3>
            <p>
                If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy
                Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at <a
                    href="mailto:contact@blakesthoughts.com"
                    >contact@blakesthoughts.com</a
                >.
            </p>
        </div>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
